properties.documentation: This defines the adapter COS interface. The adapter uses a component with this name to specify the COS PV that the adapter requires. One must exist for each adapter. The PV names are specified via the attributes: PSOS and COS

documentation.value: Specifies the value of the PSOS PV. The "type" is the data-type of the PV.
Specifies the value of the PSOS PV. The "type" is the data-type of the PV.
Specifies the name of the COS-OPREQ PV. The "type" is the type of the PV, not the type of the value.

properties.documentation: This class defines the values of the adapted PSOS states and state values.

documentation.value: The plant system is in an unknown state. Reponds to "Init""
The plant system is Off. Reponds to "Init"
The plant system is Idle. Reponds to "Start", "Stop" or "Config"

properties.documentation: This is a sub-state of the high-level adapter statemachine which has an initial state of "Off". The sub-state represents the "On" state.
Indicates that the Adapter can recover back to its last known state. If there is no last known state, it defaults to Not Ready.
